{
  "doc_id": "13676",
  "text": "Downstream of the cryostat was a steel/scintillator tail-catcher, in the same configuration as was used in a 1998 beam test [CITATION_1] , with three thick scintillator plates of 140x140 cm 2 cross-sectional area followed by four 50x50 cm 2 counters. Each counter had two outputs with gain ratio of 1:28. Signals from the last two counters were summed to keep the number of readout channels matched to the number of inputs on a LeCroy 2249A ADC.",
